description: Tylor Perry scored 21 points, making four pressure-filled free throws down the stretch, and No. 10 seed Kansas State rallied from a 10-point halftime deficit to beat seventh-seeded Texas 78-74 in the Big 12 Tournament on Wednesday night.
title: No. 10 seed Kansas State rallies to beat No. 7 seed Texas 78-74 in Big 12 Tournament

description: Led by JT Toppin's 18 points, the New Mexico Lobos defeated the Air Force Falcons 82-56 in the first round of the Mountain West Conference Tournament on Wednesday night.
title: Toppin's 18 lead New Mexico over Air Force 82-56 in Mountain West Conference Tournament

description: Jayden Taylor had 18 points and nine rebounds, and North Carolina State rolled to an 83-65 victory over Syracuse in the second round of the Atlantic Coast Conference Tournament.
title: N.C. State pulls away early in 2nd half, beats Syracuse 83-65 in ACC Tournament second round

description: Brady Cummins scored a career-high 19 points, Braeden Smith had 15 points and 12 rebounds and top-seeded Colgate collected its fourth straight Patriot League Tournament title and NCAA Tournament bid with a 74-55 win over Lehigh on Wednesday.
title: Colgate wins its fourth straight Patriot League Tournament title with 74-55 win over Lehigh

description: Kirk Cousins has a single playoff victory in his long career. Even so, the Atlanta Falcons are betting at least $100 million that he’s the quarterback who can lead this star-crossed franchise to its first Super Bowl championship.
title: Kirk Cousins looks to build his postseason legacy with the Falcons

description: A U.N. report says many countries are bouncing back from the COVID-19 pandemic, but the poorest are not and a significant number are seeing conditions in their country deteriorating.
title: UN report: Many countries are bouncing back from COVID pandemic but the poorest are not

description: Led by Josh Oduro's 20 points, the Providence Friars defeated the Georgetown Hoyas 74-56 in the Big East Conference Tournament on Wednesday night.
title: Oduro puts up 20, Providence knocks off Georgetown 74-56 in Big East Conference Tournament

description: Donta Scott scored 16 points and Maryland dominated the first 30 minutes of play in a 65-51 victory over Rutgers on the first day of the Big Ten Tournament.
title: Scott scores 16, Maryland defeats Rutgers 65-51 to advance at Big Ten Tournament

description: Davon Barnes had 15 points to lead top-seeded Sam Houston to a 78-59 victory over No. 9 seed Florida International in the Conference USA Tournament.
title: Top-seed Sam Houston opens Conference USA Tournament with 78-59 victory over FIU

description: Led by Paul Otieno's 19 points, the Quinnipiac Bobcats defeated the Canisius Golden Griffins 76-52 in a quarterfinal of the Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference Tournament.
title: Otieno's 19 lead Quinnipiac over Canisius 76-52 in Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference quarterfinal

description: Brahim Díaz has been selected in Morocco’s squad for two friendlies later this month, ending speculation about the Real Madrid winger’s possible future with the Spanish national team.
title: Brahim Díaz selected for Morocco's national team, ending speculation in Spain

description: Led by Christian Ings' 17 points, the Norfolk State Spartans defeated the Coppin State Eagles 75-51 in the Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference Tournament on Wednesday night.
title: Ings puts up 17 in Norfolk State's 75-51 win over Coppin State in MEAC Tournament

description: A person familiar with the deal says Joe Flacco is heading to the Indianapolis Colts after helping the Cleveland Browns reach the playoffs and winning the AP Comeback Player of the Year Award.
title: Joe Flacco is heading to the Colts on a 1-year, $4.5 million deal, AP source says

description: North Korea says leader Kim Jong Un has joined his troops in training to operate newly developed battle tanks and called for bigger efforts to prepare for war.
title: North Korea's Kim drives new-type tank during drills and calls for efforts to prepare for war

description: Dylan Andrews made seven 3-pointers and scored 31 points — both career-highs — to help No. 5 UCLA beat No. 12 Oregon State 67-57 in the first round of the Pac-12 Conference Tournament.
title: Andrews records career-highs with 31 points 7 3-pointers in UCLA's win over Oregon State in Pac-12

description: A person with knowledge of the deal says free agent linebacker Eric Kendricks has agreed to join the Dallas Cowboys after initially choosing the San Francisco 49ers.
title: Eric Kendricks switches to Cowboys after picking Niners in free agency, AP source says

description: The Wisconsin Court of Appeals has upheld the reckless homicide conviction of a 20-year-old in the 2018 death of his younger cousin.
title: Wisconsin appeals court upholds conviction of 20-year-old in death of younger cousin

description: The Arizona Cardinals have agreed to a $30 million, two-year deal with offensive tackle Jonah Williams, according to a person familiar with the deal.
title: Cards agree to 2-year deal with offensive tackle Jonah Williams, release veteran DJ Humphries

description: IRVINE, Calif. (AP) — An explosion during an indoor training exercise Wednesday sent 16 members of Southern California's Orange County Sheriff’s Department SWAT team to the hospital, with one person requiring surgery for a leg injury, the department said.
title: 16 SWAT officers hospitalized after blast at training facility in Southern California
